# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/common/http

### Description

The delete and set methods do not work as expected for the first param when fromString starts with a `?` i.e.

```
new HttpParams({ fromString: '?test=string' }).set('test', 'value').toString() // ?test=string&test=value instead of ?test=value
```
It's useful to support `?` because `window.location.search` starts with that character.

